Click on player names in the legend to toggle visibility. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Rankings ::: {#cell-atp-rankings .cell execution_count=5} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Rankings History"} fig = px.line( atp_rankings.sort_values('date'), x='date', y='rank', color='full_name', labels={'date': 'Year', 'rank': 'Ranking', 'full_name': 'Player'}, hover_data={'date': '|%B %Y', 'rank': True} ) fig.update_yaxes(autorange='reversed', range=[150, 1]) fig.add_hline(y=10, line_dash='dash', line_color='gray', opacity=0.5) fig.add_hline(y=1, line_dash='dash', line_color='gold', opacity=0.7) fig.update_layout( title=dict(text='ATP Rankings Journey', font=dict(size=20)), height=550, legend=dict(orientation='h', yanchor='bottom', y=-0.25, xanchor='center', x=0.5), xaxis=dict( rangeselector=dict( buttons=list([ dict(count=1, label='1Y', step='year', stepmode='backward'), dict(count=5, label='5Y', step='year', stepmode='backward'), dict(count=10, label='10Y', step='year', stepmode='backward'), dict(step='all', label='All') ]), bgcolor='rgba(150,150,150,0.1)', activecolor='#667eea' ), rangeslider=dict(visible=True, thickness=0.05), type='date' ), plot_bgcolor='rgba(0,0,0,0)', hovermode='x unified' ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#atp-rankings .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ::: # Surface Performance Tennis is played on different surfacesâ€”Hard, Clay, and Grassâ€”and players often excel on specific surfaces. Explore the heatmaps and radar charts below. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## Performance Heatmaps ::: {#cell-surface-heatmap .cell execution_count=7} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="Surface Performance Heatmaps"} def surface_record(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] row = {'Player': name} for surface in ['Hard', 'Clay', 'Grass']: surface_matches = matches_df[matches_df['surface'] == surface] wins = len(surface_matches[surface_matches['winner_id'] == pid]) losses = len(surface_matches[surface_matches['loser_id'] == pid]) total = wins + losses row[surface] = round(wins / total * 100, 1) if total >= 10 else None results.append(row) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_surface = surface_record(atp_matches, atp_players) wta_surface = surface_record(wta_matches, wta_players) fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=('ATP Surface Mastery', 'WTA Surface Mastery'), horizontal_spacing=0.12) atp_heat = atp_surface.set_index('Player')[['Hard', 'Clay', 'Grass']].dropna(how='all') wta_heat = wta_surface.set_index('Player')[['Hard', 'Clay', 'Grass']].dropna(how='all') fig.add_trace(go.Heatmap( z=atp_heat.values, x=atp_heat.columns, y=atp_heat.index, colorscale='Blues', zmin=50, zmax=95, text=[[f'{v:.1f}%' if pd.notna(v) else '' for v in row] for row in atp_heat.values], texttemplate='%{text}', textfont=dict(size=11), hovertemplate='%{y}
%{x}: %{z:.1f}%', showscale=False ), row=1, col=1) fig.add_trace(go.Heatmap( z=wta_heat.values, x=wta_heat.columns, y=wta_heat.index, colorscale='RdPu', zmin=50, zmax=95, text=[[f'{v:.1f}%' if pd.notna(v) else '' for v in row] for row in wta_heat.values], texttemplate='%{text}', textfont=dict(size=11), hovertemplate='%{y}
%{x}: %{z:.1f}%', colorbar=dict(title='Win %', x=1.02, ticksuffix='%') ), row=1, col=2) fig.update_layout(height=500, title_text='Win Percentage by Surface (min. 10 matches)') fig.show() ``` ::: {#surface-heatmap .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## Player Profiles (Radar) ::: {#cell-radar-charts .cell execution_count=8} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="Surface Profile Radar Charts"} # ATP Radar atp_top = ['Novak Djokovic', 'Carlos Alcaraz', 'Jannik Sinner', 'Alexander Zverev'] categories = ['Hard', 'Clay', 'Grass', 'Hard'] fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, specs=[[{'type': 'polar'}, {'type': 'polar'}]], subplot_titles=('ATP Top Players', 'WTA Top Players')) colors_atp = px.colors.qualitative.Set2[:4] for i, player in enumerate(atp_top): pdata = atp_surface[atp_surface['Player'] == player] if not pdata.empty: values = [pdata['Hard'].values[0], pdata['Clay'].values[0], pdata['Grass'].values[0], pdata['Hard'].values[0]] fig.add_trace(go.Scatterpolar( r=values, theta=categories, name=player.split()[-1], fill='toself', opacity=0.6, line=dict(color=colors_atp[i]) ), row=1, col=1) # WTA Radar wta_top = ['Iga Swiatek', 'Aryna Sabalenka', 'Coco Gauff', 'Elena Rybakina'] colors_wta = px.colors.qualitative.Pastel[:4] for i, player in enumerate(wta_top): pdata = wta_surface[wta_surface['Player'] == player] if not pdata.empty: values = [pdata['Hard'].values[0], pdata['Clay'].values[0], pdata['Grass'].values[0], pdata['Hard'].values[0]] fig.add_trace(go.Scatterpolar( r=values, theta=categories, name=player.split()[-1], fill='toself', opacity=0.6, line=dict(color=colors_wta[i]) ), row=1, col=2) fig.update_polars(radialaxis=dict(visible=True, range=[40, 100])) fig.update_layout(height=450, showlegend=True, legend=dict(orientation='h', yanchor='bottom', y=-0.15, xanchor='center', x=0.5)) fig.show() ``` ::: {#radar-charts .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Head-to-Head Matrix How do the top 10 players fare against each other? Green indicates a winning record, red indicates a losing record. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP H2H ::: {#cell-atp-h2h .cell execution_count=9} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Head-to-Head Matrix"} def head_to_head_matrix(matches_df, players_df): player_ids = players_df['player_id'].tolist() player_names = players_df['full_name'].tolist() h2h_matches = matches_df[(matches_df['winner_id'].isin(player_ids)) & (matches_df['loser_id'].isin(player_ids))] matrix_display = pd.DataFrame(index=player_names, columns=player_names) matrix_numeric = pd.DataFrame(index=player_names, columns=player_names, dtype=float) for i, p1_id in enumerate(player_ids): for j, p2_id in enumerate(player_ids): if i == j: matrix_display.iloc[i, j], matrix_numeric.iloc[i, j] = '-', np.nan else: wins = len(h2h_matches[(h2h_matches['winner_id'] == p1_id) & (h2h_matches['loser_id'] == p2_id)]) losses = len(h2h_matches[(h2h_matches['winner_id'] == p2_id) & (h2h_matches['loser_id'] == p1_id)]) total = wins + losses matrix_display.iloc[i, j] = f"{wins}-{losses}" if total > 0 else '0-0' matrix_numeric.iloc[i, j] = (wins / total * 100) if total > 0 else 50 return matrix_display, matrix_numeric, len(h2h_matches) atp_h2h_display, atp_h2h_numeric, atp_h2h_count = head_to_head_matrix(atp_matches, atp_players) short_names = [n.split()[-1] for n in atp_h2h_numeric.index] fig = go.Figure(data=go.Heatmap( z=atp_h2h_numeric.values, x=short_names, y=short_names, colorscale='RdYlGn', zmin=0, zmax=100, text=atp_h2h_display.values, texttemplate='%{text}', hovertemplate='%{y} vs %{x}
Record: %{text}
Win Rate: %{z:.0f}%', colorbar=dict(title='Win %', ticksuffix='%') )) fig.update_layout( title=f'ATP Head-to-Head ({atp_h2h_count} matches between Top 10)', height=550, xaxis_title='Opponent', yaxis_title='Player', yaxis=dict(autorange='reversed') ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#atp-h2h .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ::: # Serve Analysis The serve is crucial in tennis. Explore ace rates, double faults, and serve effectiveness. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-serve-analysis-atp .cell execution_count=11} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Serve Statistics"} def calculate_serve_stats(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid][['w_ace', 'w_df', 'w_1stIn', 'w_svpt', 'w_1stWon', 'w_2ndWon']].copy() wins.columns = ['aces', 'df', '1st_in', 'svpt', '1st_won', '2nd_won'] losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid][['l_ace', 'l_df', 'l_1stIn', 'l_svpt', 'l_1stWon', 'l_2ndWon']].copy() losses.columns = ['aces', 'df', '1st_in', 'svpt', '1st_won', '2nd_won'] all_m = pd.concat([wins, losses]).dropna() if len(all_m) > 0: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'Aces/Match': round(all_m['aces'].mean(), 1), 'DFs/Match': round(all_m['df'].mean(), 1), '1st Serve %': round((all_m['1st_in'] / all_m['svpt']).mean() * 100, 1), '1st Win %': round((all_m['1st_won'] / all_m['1st_in']).mean() * 100, 1), '2nd Win %': round((all_m['2nd_won'] / (all_m['svpt'] - all_m['1st_in'])).mean() * 100, 1) }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_serve = calculate_serve_stats(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=('Aces vs Double Faults', 'Serve Win Percentages'), horizontal_spacing=0.15) fig.add_trace(go.Scatter( x=atp_serve['Aces/Match'], y=atp_serve['DFs/Match'], mode='markers+text', text=atp_serve['Player'].str.split().str[-1], textposition='top center', marker=dict(size=15, color='#1f77b4'), hovertemplate='%{text}
Aces: %{x}
DFs: %{y}' ), row=1, col=1) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_serve['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_serve['1st Win %'], name='1st Serve Win %', marker_color='#2ecc71' ), row=1, col=2) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_serve['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_serve['2nd Win %'], name='2nd Serve Win %', marker_color='#e74c3c' ), row=1, col=2) fig.update_layout(height=450, showlegend=True, legend=dict(orientation='h', y=-0.15), title_text='ATP Serve Analysis') fig.update_xaxes(title_text='Aces per Match', row=1, col=1) fig.update_yaxes(title_text='Double Faults per Match', row=1, col=1) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45, row=1, col=2) fig.update_yaxes(title_text='Win %', row=1, col=2) fig.show() ``` ::: {#serve-analysis-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ::: # Yearly Performance Track player performance year over year with interactive range selection. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Yearly Wins ::: {#cell-atp-yearly .cell execution_count=13} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Yearly Performance"} def yearly_wins(matches_df, players_df, start_year=2018): matches_df = matches_df[matches_df['tourney_date'].dt.year >= start_year].copy() matches_df['year'] = matches_df['tourney_date'].dt.year results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] for year in range(start_year, 2025): year_matches = matches_df[matches_df['year'] == year] wins = len(year_matches[year_matches['winner_id'] == pid]) losses = len(year_matches[year_matches['loser_id'] == pid]) total = wins + losses results.append({'Player': name, 'Year': year, 'Wins': wins, 'Losses': losses, 'Win %': round(wins / total * 100, 1) if total > 0 else 0}) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_yearly = yearly_wins(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = px.line(atp_yearly, x='Year', y='Wins', color='Player', markers=True, hover_data={'Win %': True, 'Losses': True}, title='ATP Yearly Match Wins (2018-2024)') fig.update_layout( height=500, legend=dict(orientation='h', yanchor='bottom', y=-0.3, xanchor='center', x=0.5), xaxis=dict(rangeslider=dict(visible=True, thickness=0.05), tickmode='linear', dtick=1) ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#atp-yearly .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Yearly Wins ::: {#cell-wta-yearly .cell execution_count=14} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Yearly Performance"} wta_yearly = yearly_wins(wta_matches, wta_players) fig = px.line(wta_yearly, x='Year', y='Wins', color='Player', markers=True, hover_data={'Win %': True, 'Losses': True}, title='WTA Yearly Match Wins (2018-2024)') fig.update_layout( height=500, legend=dict(orientation='h', yanchor='bottom', y=-0.3, xanchor='center', x=0.5), xaxis=dict(rangeslider=dict(visible=True, thickness=0.05), tickmode='linear', dtick=1) ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#wta-yearly .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ::: # Match Duration Analysis How long do matches last? Explore the rhythm of tennisâ€”from quick demolitions to marathon battles. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-match-duration-atp .cell execution_count=17} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Match Duration Analysis"} def analyze_duration(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid][['minutes', 'best_of']].copy() wins['result'] = 'Win' losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid][['minutes', 'best_of']].copy() losses['result'] = 'Loss' all_m = pd.concat([wins, losses]).dropna() all_m['Player'] = name results.append(all_m) return pd.concat(results, ignore_index=True) if results else pd.DataFrame() atp_duration = analyze_duration(atp_matches, atp_players) # Stats by player atp_stats = atp_duration.groupby('Player').agg( avg_duration=('minutes', 'mean'), max_duration=('minutes', 'max'), matches=('minutes', 'count') ).reset_index().round(1) fig = make_subplots(rows=1, cols=2, subplot_titles=('Match Duration Distribution', 'Average Duration by Player'), horizontal_spacing=0.12) # Histogram fig.add_trace(go.Histogram(x=atp_duration['minutes'], nbinsx=30, marker_color='#1f77b4', opacity=0.7, name='All Matches'), row=1, col=1) # Bar chart fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_stats.sort_values('avg_duration')['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_stats.sort_values('avg_duration')['avg_duration'], marker_color='#1f77b4', text=atp_stats.sort_values('avg_duration')['avg_duration'], textposition='outside' ), row=1, col=2) fig.update_layout(height=400, showlegend=False, title_text='ATP Match Duration') fig.update_xaxes(title_text='Minutes', row=1, col=1) fig.update_yaxes(title_text='Number of Matches', row=1, col=1) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45, row=1, col=2) fig.update_yaxes(title_text='Avg Minutes', row=1, col=2) fig.show() ``` ::: {#match-duration-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ::: # Mental Toughness: Break Points Break points are where matches are won and lost. Saving break points shows mental fortitude; converting them shows killer instinct. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-break-points-atp .cell execution_count=19} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Break Point Analysis"} def calculate_bp_stats(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid] losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid] # Break points SAVED (on serve) bp_faced_w = wins['w_bpFaced'].sum() bp_saved_w = wins['w_bpSaved'].sum() bp_faced_l = losses['l_bpFaced'].sum() bp_saved_l = losses['l_bpSaved'].sum() total_faced = bp_faced_w + bp_faced_l total_saved = bp_saved_w + bp_saved_l # Break points CONVERTED (on return) bp_opp_faced_w = wins['l_bpFaced'].sum() bp_opp_saved_w = wins['l_bpSaved'].sum() bp_opp_faced_l = losses['w_bpFaced'].sum() bp_opp_saved_l = losses['w_bpSaved'].sum() total_bp_chances = bp_opp_faced_w + bp_opp_faced_l total_converted = (bp_opp_faced_w - bp_opp_saved_w) + (bp_opp_faced_l - bp_opp_saved_l) if total_faced > 0 and total_bp_chances > 0: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'BP Save %': round(total_saved / total_faced * 100, 1), 'BP Convert %': round(total_converted / total_bp_chances * 100, 1), 'BP Faced': int(total_faced), 'BP Chances': int(total_bp_chances) }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_bp = calculate_bp_stats(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Scatter( x=atp_bp['BP Save %'], y=atp_bp['BP Convert %'], mode='markers+text', text=atp_bp['Player'].str.split().str[-1], textposition='top center', marker=dict(size=15, color='#1f77b4'), hovertemplate='%{text}
Save: %{x}%
Convert: %{y}%' )) # Add quadrant lines avg_save = atp_bp['BP Save %'].mean() avg_conv = atp_bp['BP Convert %'].mean() fig.add_hline(y=avg_conv, line_dash="dash", line_color="gray", opacity=0.5) fig.add_vline(x=avg_save, line_dash="dash", line_color="gray", opacity=0.5) fig.update_layout( height=500, title='ATP Break Point Performance', xaxis_title='Break Point Save %', yaxis_title='Break Point Conversion %', annotations=[ dict(x=0.95, y=0.95, xref='paper', yref='paper', text='Elite: Save & Convert', showarrow=False), dict(x=0.05, y=0.05, xref='paper', yref='paper', text='Needs Work', showarrow=False) ] ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#break-points-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}

Save: %{x}%
Convert: %{y}%' )) avg_save = wta_bp['BP Save %'].mean() avg_conv = wta_bp['BP Convert %'].mean() fig.add_hline(y=avg_conv, line_dash="dash", line_color="gray", opacity=0.5) fig.add_vline(x=avg_save, line_dash="dash", line_color="gray", opacity=0.5) fig.update_layout( height=500, title='WTA Break Point Performance', xaxis_title='Break Point Save %', yaxis_title='Break Point Conversion %', annotations=[ dict(x=0.95, y=0.95, xref='paper', yref='paper', text='Elite: Save & Convert', showarrow=False), dict(x=0.05, y=0.05, xref='paper', yref='paper', text='Needs Work', showarrow=False) ] ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#break-points-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Tournament Level Performance Not all tournaments are equal. Grand Slams are the ultimate test (best of 5 for men), followed by Masters 1000 and other tiers. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-tournament-level-atp .cell execution_count=21} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Tournament Level Analysis"} level_names = { 'G': 'Grand Slam', 'M': 'Masters 1000', 'A': 'ATP 500/250', 'F': 'Tour Finals', 'D': 'Davis Cup', 'C': 'Challengers' } level_order = ['Grand Slam', 'Tour Finals', 'Masters 1000', 'ATP 500/250', 'Davis Cup'] def tourney_level_stats(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] for level, level_name in level_names.items(): level_matches = matches_df[matches_df['tourney_level'] == level] wins = len(level_matches[level_matches['winner_id'] == pid]) losses = len(level_matches[level_matches['loser_id'] == pid]) total = wins + losses if total >= 5: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'Level': level_name, 'Wins': wins, 'Losses': losses, 'Win %': round(wins / total * 100, 1), 'Matches': total }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_level = tourney_level_stats(atp_matches, atp_players) atp_pivot = atp_level.pivot(index='Player', columns='Level', values='Win %') atp_pivot = atp_pivot[[c for c in level_order if c in atp_pivot.columns]] fig = go.Figure(data=go.Heatmap( z=atp_pivot.values, x=atp_pivot.columns, y=atp_pivot.index, colorscale='Blues', zmin=50, zmax=95, text=[[f'{v:.0f}%' if pd.notna(v) else '' for v in row] for row in atp_pivot.values], texttemplate='%{text}', textfont=dict(size=11), hovertemplate='%{y}
%{x}: %{z:.1f}%' )) fig.update_layout( height=450, title='ATP Win % by Tournament Level', xaxis_title='Tournament Level', yaxis_title='Player' ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#tournament-level-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-tournament-level-wta .cell execution_count=22} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Tournament Level Analysis"} wta_level_names = { 'G': 'Grand Slam', 'P': 'WTA 1000', 'PM': 'WTA 500', 'I': 'WTA 250', 'F': 'Tour Finals', 'D': 'BJK Cup' } wta_level_order = ['Grand Slam', 'Tour Finals', 'WTA 1000', 'WTA 500', 'WTA 250'] def wta_tourney_level_stats(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] for level, level_name in wta_level_names.items(): level_matches = matches_df[matches_df['tourney_level'] == level] wins = len(level_matches[level_matches['winner_id'] == pid]) losses = len(level_matches[level_matches['loser_id'] == pid]) total = wins + losses if total >= 5: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'Level': level_name, 'Wins': wins, 'Losses': losses, 'Win %': round(wins / total * 100, 1), 'Matches': total }) return pd.DataFrame(results) wta_level = wta_tourney_level_stats(wta_matches, wta_players) wta_pivot = wta_level.pivot(index='Player', columns='Level', values='Win %') wta_pivot = wta_pivot[[c for c in wta_level_order if c in wta_pivot.columns]] fig = go.Figure(data=go.Heatmap( z=wta_pivot.values, x=wta_pivot.columns, y=wta_pivot.index, colorscale='RdPu', zmin=50, zmax=95, text=[[f'{v:.0f}%' if pd.notna(v) else '' for v in row] for row in wta_pivot.values], texttemplate='%{text}', textfont=dict(size=11), hovertemplate='%{y}
%{x}: %{z:.1f}%' )) fig.update_layout( height=450, title='WTA Win % by Tournament Level', xaxis_title='Tournament Level', yaxis_title='Player' ) fig.show() ``` ::: {#tournament-level-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Round-by-Round Progression How deep do players typically go in tournaments? This shows where players exit. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-round-progression-atp .cell execution_count=23} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Round Progression Analysis"} round_order = ['R128', 'R64', 'R32', 'R16', 'QF', 'SF', 'F', 'W'] def round_progression(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid].groupby('round').size() final_wins = len(matches_df[(matches_df['winner_id'] == pid) & (matches_df['round'] == 'F')]) row = {'Player': name} for r in round_order[:-1]: row[r] = losses.get(r, 0) row['W'] = final_wins results.append(row) df = pd.DataFrame(results) df['Total'] = df[round_order].sum(axis=1) return df atp_rounds = round_progression(atp_matches, atp_players) colors = ['#440154', '#482878', '#3e4989', '#31688e', '#26828e', '#1f9e89', '#35b779', '#6ece58'] fig = go.Figure() for i, r in enumerate(round_order): fig.add_trace(go.Bar( name=r if r != 'W' else 'Title', x=atp_rounds['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_rounds[r], marker_color=colors[i] )) fig.update_layout( barmode='stack', height=450, title='ATP Tournament Exit Distribution', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Number of Tournaments', legend_title='Exit Round' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#round-progression-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-round-progression-wta .cell execution_count=24} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Round Progression Analysis"} wta_rounds = round_progression(wta_matches, wta_players) colors_wta = ['#7b2d8e', '#8e3a9e', '#a147ae', '#b454be', '#c761ce', '#da6ede', '#ed7bee', '#ff88ff'] fig = go.Figure() for i, r in enumerate(round_order): fig.add_trace(go.Bar( name=r if r != 'W' else 'Title', x=wta_rounds['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_rounds[r], marker_color=colors_wta[i] )) fig.update_layout( barmode='stack', height=450, title='WTA Tournament Exit Distribution', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Number of Tournaments', legend_title='Exit Round' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#round-progression-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Age & Performance Curves Tennis players typically peak in their mid-20s. How do these top players perform at different ages? ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-age-curves-atp .cell execution_count=25} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Age Performance Analysis"} def age_performance(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid][['tourney_date', 'winner_age']].copy() wins.columns = ['date', 'age'] wins['result'] = 1 losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid][['tourney_date', 'loser_age']].copy() losses.columns = ['date', 'age'] losses['result'] = 0 all_m = pd.concat([wins, losses]).dropna() all_m['age_bin'] = (all_m['age'] // 1).astype(int) all_m['Player'] = name results.append(all_m) return pd.concat(results, ignore_index=True) if results else pd.DataFrame() atp_age = age_performance(atp_matches, atp_players) atp_age_agg = atp_age.groupby(['Player', 'age_bin']).agg( wins=('result', 'sum'), matches=('result', 'count') ).reset_index() atp_age_agg['win_pct'] = (atp_age_agg['wins'] / atp_age_agg['matches'] * 100).round(1) atp_age_agg = atp_age_agg[atp_age_agg['matches'] >= 10] fig = px.line( atp_age_agg, x='age_bin', y='win_pct', color='Player', title='ATP Win % by Age', labels={'age_bin': 'Age', 'win_pct': 'Win %', 'Player': 'Player'}, markers=True ) fig.update_layout(height=450, xaxis_title='Age', yaxis_title='Win %') fig.show() ``` ::: {#age-curves-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-age-curves-wta .cell execution_count=26} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Age Performance Analysis"} wta_age = age_performance(wta_matches, wta_players) wta_age_agg = wta_age.groupby(['Player', 'age_bin']).agg( wins=('result', 'sum'), matches=('result', 'count') ).reset_index() wta_age_agg['win_pct'] = (wta_age_agg['wins'] / wta_age_agg['matches'] * 100).round(1) wta_age_agg = wta_age_agg[wta_age_agg['matches'] >= 10] fig = px.line( wta_age_agg, x='age_bin', y='win_pct', color='Player', title='WTA Win % by Age', labels={'age_bin': 'Age', 'win_pct': 'Win %', 'Player': 'Player'}, markers=True, color_discrete_sequence=px.colors.qualitative.Pastel ) fig.update_layout(height=450, xaxis_title='Age', yaxis_title='Win %') fig.show() ``` ::: {#age-curves-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Seed vs Result: Upset Analysis Do players live up to their seeding? Who causes upsets, and who suffers them? ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-upset-analysis-atp .cell execution_count=27} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Upset Analysis"} def upset_analysis(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid].copy() losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid].copy() upsets_caused = 0 upsets_suffered = 0 for _, match in wins.iterrows(): w_seed = match['winner_seed'] if pd.notna(match['winner_seed']) else 999 l_seed = match['loser_seed'] if pd.notna(match['loser_seed']) else 999 try: w_seed, l_seed = int(w_seed), int(l_seed) except: continue if w_seed > l_seed: upsets_caused += 1 for _, match in losses.iterrows(): w_seed = match['winner_seed'] if pd.notna(match['winner_seed']) else 999 l_seed = match['loser_seed'] if pd.notna(match['loser_seed']) else 999 try: w_seed, l_seed = int(w_seed), int(l_seed) except: continue if w_seed > l_seed: upsets_suffered += 1 total_matches = len(wins) + len(losses) if total_matches > 0: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'Upsets Caused': upsets_caused, 'Upsets Suffered': upsets_suffered, 'Net Upsets': upsets_caused - upsets_suffered }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_upsets = upset_analysis(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Upsets Caused'], name='Upsets Caused', marker_color='#2ecc71' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=-atp_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Upsets Suffered'], name='Upsets Suffered', marker_color='#e74c3c' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='relative', height=450, title='ATP Upset Balance (Caused vs Suffered)', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Number of Upsets' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#upset-analysis-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-upset-analysis-wta .cell execution_count=28} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Upset Analysis"} wta_upsets = upset_analysis(wta_matches, wta_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Upsets Caused'], name='Upsets Caused', marker_color='#2ecc71' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=-wta_upsets.sort_values('Net Upsets')['Upsets Suffered'], name='Upsets Suffered', marker_color='#e74c3c' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='relative', height=450, title='WTA Upset Balance (Caused vs Suffered)', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Number of Upsets' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#upset-analysis-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Score Patterns & Match Dynamics How do players win? Dominant straight-set victories or grinding 3-setters? ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-score-patterns-atp .cell execution_count=29} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Score Pattern Analysis"} import re def parse_score(score): if pd.isna(score) or score in ['W/O', 'DEF', 'RET', 'ABN', 'walkover']: return None, None, 0 sets = str(score).split() winner_sets = loser_sets = tiebreaks = 0 for s in sets: if '(' in s: tiebreaks += 1 match = re.match(r'(\d+)-(\d+)', s) if match: g1, g2 = int(match.group(1)), int(match.group(2)) if g1 > g2: winner_sets += 1 else: loser_sets += 1 return winner_sets, loser_sets, tiebreaks def analyze_scores(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid] losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid] straight_wins = deciding_wins = straight_losses = deciding_losses = 0 for _, match in wins.iterrows(): ws, ls, _ = parse_score(match['score']) if ws is not None: if ls == 0: straight_wins += 1 else: deciding_wins += 1 for _, match in losses.iterrows(): ws, ls, _ = parse_score(match['score']) if ws is not None: if ws - ls == 1: deciding_losses += 1 else: straight_losses += 1 total_wins = straight_wins + deciding_wins total_losses = straight_losses + deciding_losses if total_wins > 0 and total_losses > 0: results.append({ 'Player': name, 'Straight Set Win %': round(straight_wins / total_wins * 100, 1), 'Deciding Set Win %': round(deciding_wins / total_wins * 100, 1), 'Straight Set Loss %': round(straight_losses / total_losses * 100, 1) }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_scores = analyze_scores(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_scores['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_scores['Straight Set Win %'], name='Straight Set Wins', marker_color='#2ecc71' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_scores['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_scores['Deciding Set Win %'], name='Deciding Set Wins', marker_color='#3498db' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='stack', height=450, title='ATP Win Patterns: Straight Sets vs Deciding Sets', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='% of Wins' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#score-patterns-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-score-patterns-wta .cell execution_count=30} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Score Pattern Analysis"} wta_scores = analyze_scores(wta_matches, wta_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_scores['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_scores['Straight Set Win %'], name='Straight Set Wins', marker_color='#2ecc71' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_scores['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_scores['Deciding Set Win %'], name='Deciding Set Wins', marker_color='#9b59b6' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='stack', height=450, title='WTA Win Patterns: Straight Sets vs Deciding Sets', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='% of Wins' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#score-patterns-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ::: # Return Game Analysis Tennis is a game of serve and return. Great returners can neutralize big servers. ::: {.panel-tabset} ## ATP Tour ::: {#cell-return-analysis-atp .cell execution_count=31} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="ATP Return Game Statistics"} def calculate_return_stats(matches_df, players_df): results = [] for _, player in players_df.iterrows(): pid, name = player['player_id'], player['full_name'] wins = matches_df[matches_df['winner_id'] == pid][['l_svpt', 'l_1stIn', 'l_1stWon', 'l_2ndWon']].copy() wins.columns = ['svpt', '1stIn', '1stWon', '2ndWon'] losses = matches_df[matches_df['loser_id'] == pid][['w_svpt', 'w_1stIn', 'w_1stWon', 'w_2ndWon']].copy() losses.columns = ['svpt', '1stIn', '1stWon', '2ndWon'] all_m = pd.concat([wins, losses]).dropna() if len(all_m) > 50: total_1st_return_pts = all_m['1stIn'].sum() pts_won_vs_1st = total_1st_return_pts - all_m['1stWon'].sum() total_2nd_return_pts = all_m['svpt'].sum() - all_m['1stIn'].sum() pts_won_vs_2nd = total_2nd_return_pts - all_m['2ndWon'].sum() results.append({ 'Player': name, '1st Return %': round(pts_won_vs_1st / total_1st_return_pts * 100, 1), '2nd Return %': round(pts_won_vs_2nd / total_2nd_return_pts * 100, 1) }) return pd.DataFrame(results) atp_return = calculate_return_stats(atp_matches, atp_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_return['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_return['1st Return %'], name='vs 1st Serve', marker_color='#3498db' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=atp_return['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=atp_return['2nd Return %'], name='vs 2nd Serve', marker_color='#e67e22' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='group', height=450, title='ATP Return Points Won %', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Points Won %' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#return-analysis-atp .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
``` ::: ::: ## WTA Tour ::: {#cell-return-analysis-wta .cell execution_count=32} ``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="WTA Return Game Statistics"} wta_return = calculate_return_stats(wta_matches, wta_players) fig = go.Figure() fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_return['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_return['1st Return %'], name='vs 1st Serve', marker_color='#9b59b6' )) fig.add_trace(go.Bar( x=wta_return['Player'].str.split().str[-1], y=wta_return['2nd Return %'], name='vs 2nd Serve', marker_color='#e67e22' )) fig.update_layout( barmode='group', height=450, title='WTA Return Points Won %', xaxis_title='Player', yaxis_title='Points Won %' ) fig.update_xaxes(tickangle=45) fig.show() ``` ::: {#return-analysis-wta .cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
